X_i \in \{0,1\}
X=\sum_{i=1}^n X_i
\delta>0
\Pr\left(X \ge (1+\delta)EX \right) \le e^{-c\cdot(EX)\delta ^2},
c
X_1,\ldots,X_n
X_i \in \{0,1\}
m
\Pr\left( \sum_{i=1}^n \mathbb{E}[X_i|X_{<i}] \le m\right) = 1.
X=\sum_{i=1}^n X_i
\lambda > 0
\Pr\left(X \ge m+\lambda \right) \le e^{-2 \lambda^2/n}.
